TITLE: Initializing WooCommerce API Client via HTTPClientFactory (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to import, configure, and instantiate a WooCommerce API client using the HTTPClientFactory. It covers both basic and OAuth authentication. The client object provides the main interface for making API requests; the example shows fetching product data with client.get and handling API responses and errors. Requires '@woocommerce/api' as a dependency, and authentication credentials for the target WooCommerce site. Intended for use in Node.js or browser (with appropriate build tools).
