TITLE: Combining Multiple Cart and Checkout Filters in WooCommerce with TSX
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to combine various WooCommerce filters to customize the order summary. It filters cart item classes, prices, item names, and subtotal price formats based on the context, specifically targeting the order summary context.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/docs/cart-and-checkout-blocks/available-filters/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const { registerCheckoutFilters } = window.wc.blocksCheckout;

const isOrderSummaryContext = ( args ) => args?.context === 'summary';

const modifyCartItemClass = ( defaultValue, extensions, args ) => {
	if ( isOrderSummaryContext( args ) ) {
		return 'my-custom-class';
	}
	return defaultValue;
};

const modifyCartItemPrice = ( defaultValue, extensions, args ) => {
	if ( isOrderSummaryContext( args ) ) {
		return '&lt;price/&gt; for all items';
	}
	return defaultValue;
};

const modifyItemName = ( defaultValue, extensions, args ) => {
	if ( isOrderSummaryContext( args ) ) {
		return `${ defaultValue }`;
	}
	return defaultValue;
};

const modifySubtotalPriceFormat = ( defaultValue, extensions, args ) => {
	if ( isOrderSummaryContext( args ) ) {
		return '&lt;price/&gt; per item';
	}
	return defaultValue;
};

registerCheckoutFilters( 'example-extension', {
	cartItemClass: modifyCartItemClass,
	cartItemPrice: modifyCartItemPrice,
	itemName: modifyItemName,
	subtotalPriceFormat: modifySubtotalPriceFormat,
} );
```

