TITLE: Displaying WooCommerce Product Custom Fields in PHP
DESCRIPTION: PHP function that displays a custom field value on single product pages after the short description. The function checks if it's a product page, gets the product object, retrieves the custom field value using get_post_meta(), and displays it if not empty.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/docs/code-snippets/displaying_custom_fields_in_your_theme_or_site.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

// Display a product custom field within single product pages after the short description 

function woocommerce_custom_field_example() {

    if ( ! is_product() ) {
        return;
    }

    global $product;

    if ( ! is_object( $product ) ) {
        $product = wc_get_product( get_the_ID() );
    }

    $custom_field_value = get_post_meta( $product->get_id(), 'woo_custom_field', true );

    if ( ! empty( $custom_field_value ) ) {
       echo '&lt;div class="custom-field"&gt;' . esc_html( $custom_field_value ) . '&lt;/div&gt;';
    }
}

add_action( 'woocommerce_before_add_to_cart_form', 'woocommerce_custom_field_example', 10 );
```

