TITLE: Rendering Block Templates with WooCommerce Hooks in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Provides a high-level explanation of the render_block_template() method, which is registered with the 'template_redirect' filter to conditionally enable block templates in WooCommerce before the WordPress template is selected. The method checks whether a block template should load, applies the 'woocommerce_has_block_template' filter to influence rendering, and may disable a compatibility layer using another filter. This method does not accept parameters or return a value; instead, it sets up filter hooks for the rendering process. Dependencies include the WooCommerce core and WordPress filter APIs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/plugins/woocommerce/client/blocks/docs/internal-developers/templates/individual-template-classes.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
// render_block_template() is registered on the 'template_redirect' filter
// It determines if a block template should render for the current page request
// and calls appropriate WooCommerce filters.

add_filter( 'template_redirect', 'render_block_template' );

function render_block_template() {
    // Check if should use block template and override via filter
    if ( should_load_block_template() ) {
        add_filter( 'woocommerce_has_block_template', '__return_true' );
    }
    // Optionally disable compatibility layer under certain conditions
    if ( page_contains_legacy_block() ) {
        add_filter( 'woocommerce_disable_compatibility_layer', '__return_true' );
    }
    // No return value
}

```

