TITLE: Implementing Lifecycle Hooks in PHP for WooCommerce Function
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add 'before' and 'after' lifecycle hooks to a WooCommerce function, along with an optional filter for the return value. This pattern allows observation of the function's lifecycle and modification of its result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/docs/extension-development/adding-actions-and-filters.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
function woocommerce_get_current_promotions( ...$args ) {
    /* Any initial prep, then first lifecycle hook... */
    do_action( 'woocommerce_before_get_current_promotions', $args );
    /* ...Do actual work, then final lifecycle hook... */
    do_action( 'woocommerce_after_get_current_promotions', $result, $args );
    /* ...Return the result, optionally via a filter... */
    return apply_filters( 'woocommerce_get_current_promotions', $result, $args );
}
```

