TITLE: Subscribing to onCheckoutFail Event in Internal WooCommerce Development (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to subscribe to the onCheckoutFail event using the useCheckoutContext hook in internal WooCommerce development. It uses the useEffect hook to set up and clean up the event subscription.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/plugins/woocommerce/client/blocks/docs/internal-developers/block-client-apis/checkout/checkout-flow-and-events.md#2025-04-23_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useCheckoutContext } from '@woocommerce/base-contexts';
import { useEffect } from '@wordpress/element';

const Component = () => {
	const { onCheckoutFail } = useCheckoutContext();
	useEffect( () => {
		const unsubscribe = onCheckoutFail( () => true );
		return unsubscribe;
	}, [ onCheckoutFail ] );
	return null;
};
```

