TITLE: Registering a WordPress Handler for Adding WooCommerce Blocks
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to register a WordPress specific handler to add WooCommerce blocks to a store template using the 'woocommerce/add-block-template' hook. It passes block name, template name, and other attributes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/packages/js/product-editor/src/components/block-slot-fill/Readme.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { registerPlugin } from '@wordpress/plugins';
import { addFilter } from '@wordpress/hooks';
import { useWooBlockProps } from '@woocommerce/block-templates';
import { ProductGallery } from '@woocommerce/blocks-components';

// WordPress Editor specific handler.
addFilter(
    'woocommerce/add-block-template',
    'woocommerce/add-block-template-wp-editor',
    ( blockTemplates, blockName, templateName, attributes ) => {
        if ( blockName === 'woocommerce/product-gallery' ) {
            blockTemplates.wordpress = () => {
                const blockProps = useWooBlockProps( attributes );

                return (
                    <div { ...blockProps }>
                        <ProductGallery
                            className={ attributes.className }
                        />
                    </div>
                );
            };
        }

        return blockTemplates;
    }
);
```

