TITLE: Creating Playwright Fixture for Handlebars Templates in WooCommerce E2E Tests - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet shows how to define a custom Playwright fixture (filteredProductsTemplate) using utilities from '@woocommerce/e2e-utils'. The fixture uses requestUtils.createTemplateFromFile to provide a TemplateCompiler for Handlebars templates, enabling parameterized compilation with dynamic data in tests. Dependencies include Playwright and WooCommerce's E2E testing utilities, and the key parameter is the template file name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/plugins/woocommerce/client/blocks/docs/contributors/e2e-guidelines.md#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
// tests/product-collection.spec.ts

import { test as base, expect, TemplateCompiler } from '@woocommerce/e2e-utils';

const test = base.extend< {
	filteredProductsTemplate: TemplateCompiler;
} >( {
	filteredProductsTemplate: async ( { requestUtils }, use ) => {
		const compiler = await requestUtils.createTemplateFromFile(
			'archive-product_with-filters'
		);
		await use( compiler );
	},
} );
```

