DESCRIPTION: Illustrates a 'lazy' dependency resolution approach. Instead of injecting specific services, the PSR-11 `ContainerInterface` itself is injected via the `init` method. Dependencies (`Service1` in this case) are then resolved explicitly using the container's `get` method only when needed within other methods. This is generally discouraged in favor of direct method injection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/woocommerce/woocommerce/blob/trunk/plugins/woocommerce/src/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use TheService1Namespace\Service1;

class TheClassWithDependencies {
    private $container;

    public function init( \Psr\Container\ContainerInterface $container ) {
        $this->$container = $container;
    }

    public function method_that_needs_service_1() {
        $this->container->get( Service1::class )->do_something();
    }
}
```

